# Cloud Management Tools

## Web-based
- Firewall
- Commonly used

## Command Line
- Command Line Interface (CLI)
- PowerShell 

## REST API
- Application Programming Interface (API)
- Entire management through an API (e.g., Google). Third parties can use your program.

# Web-based Cloud Management
- AWS, GCP & Azure

# Command Line Cloud Management 

## AWS
- AWS CLI
- PowerShell

## Azure
- Azure CLI
- Azure PowerShell: 
    ```powershell
    Install-Module -Name Az -AllowClobber -Scope CurrentUser
    ```

## Google Cloud
- Google Cloud SDK (Software Developer Kit)
- Component management (kubectl)
- Cloud tool for PowerShell

## Cloud Shell 

# Cloud API (Postman)
- POST
- PUT
- DELETE
- GET
- PATCH

# Practice 

## Azure
- Networking
- Find my IP address
- Use SSH

### AzureShell
- List virtual machines:
    ```sh
    az vm list
    ```

## AWS
- EC2
- Instances (running)
- t2.micro: click on instance ID
- Scroll down to TCP protocol in Security
- Click on security group
- Edit inbound rules
- Add my IP address

### CloudShell 
- Describe instances:
    ```sh
    aws ec2 describe-instances
    ```

## GCP
- Compute Engine
- Click on Demo
- Scroll down to Network interfaces & click
- Click on Network interfaces details
- Firewall rules
- Click on ssh
- Edit my IP ranges

### GCPShell
- List compute instances:
    ```sh
    gcloud compute instances list
    ```
